⚙️ 1. Prerequisites (for all OS)

Before you start:

Node.js ≥ 18 must be installed

Check:

node -v
npm -v


If not installed, download from https://nodejs.org

🪟 For Windows (Command Prompt / PowerShell)
# 1️⃣ Navigate to your desired folder
cd Desktop

# 2️⃣ Create a new Vite + React project
npm create vite@latest my-react-app -- --template react

# 3️⃣ Move into the project directory
cd my-react-app

# 4️⃣ Install dependencies
npm install

# 5️⃣ Start the development server
npm run dev


💡 Tip:
If using PowerShell, make sure execution policy allows scripts:

Set-ExecutionPolicy -ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Scope CurrentUser

🍎 For macOS (Terminal / iTerm)
# 1️⃣ Navigate to your desired folder
cd ~/Desktop

# 2️⃣ Create a new React project using Vite
npm create vite@latest my-react-app -- --template react

# 3️⃣ Go into the project folder
cd my-react-app

# 4️⃣ Install dependencies
npm install

# 5️⃣ Start the dev server
npm run dev


💡 Optional: Use pnpm or yarn instead of npm
Example:

pnpm create vite my-react-app --template react

🐧 For Linux (Ubuntu, Fedora, etc.)
# 1️⃣ Update and install Node.js (if needed)
sudo apt update
sudo apt install nodejs npm -y

# 2️⃣ Verify installation
node -v
npm -v

# 3️⃣ Create Vite + React project
npm create vite@latest my-react-app -- --template react

# 4️⃣ Move to project folder
cd my-react-app

# 5️⃣ Install dependencies
npm install

# 6️⃣ Start development server
npm run dev


💡 Note:
If you face permission errors, prefix with sudo or fix npm permissions:

sudo chown -R $USER:$GROUP ~/.npm

🚀 Run the Project

Once npm run dev runs successfully, you’ll see output like:

  VITE vX.X.X  ready in 500ms
  ➜  Local:   http://localhost:5173/


Open that URL in your browser to view your React app 🎉